
.TH LOOPE 7 "17 Feb 2015" "8086 ASM" "Sheridan College Comp Arch 8086 Instrcution's set"
.SH INSTRUCTION
LOOPE
.SH OPERANDS


	label



.SH DESCRIPTION

Decrease CX, jump to label if CX not zero and Equal (ZF = 1). Algorithm:



CX = CX - 1
if (CX &lt;> 0) and (ZF = 1) then
	
	jump
	
	else
	
	no jump, continue
	



	
	example for emu8086 emulator:

; Loop until result fits into AL alone,
; or 5 times. The result will be over 255
; on third loop (100+100+100),
; so loop will exit.
   include 'emu8086.inc'
   ORG 100h
   MOV AX, 0
   MOV CX, 5
label1:
   PUTC '*'
   ADD AX, 100
   CMP AH, 0
   LOOPE label1
   RET



 C Z S O P A 
 unchanged 


